{
  "text": "The GENPOD trial [CITATION_1] ) was designed to test two primary hypotheses regarding (1) genetic and (2) clinical predictors of response to antidepressant medication. There was no evidence that the genetic serotonin polymorphism 5-HTTLPR (Lewis et al. 2011) or severity of depression [CITATION_2] was associated with response to antidepressant medication. Secondary analysis of these trial data can provide information on the comparative efficacy of an SSRI (citalopram) and an NaRI (reboxetine).",
